f%20costs%20on%20to%20shoppers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223239%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20customer%20shops%20at%20a%20T.J.%20Maxx%20store%20on%20May%2021%2C%202025%20in%20Chicago%2C%20Illinois.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a60ee1a17a8c5b40532daa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222154%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETJX%20negotiates%20a%20price%20it%20is%20willing%20to%20pay%20for%20goods%20based%20on%20what%20a%20shopper%20would%20spend%20elsewhere%20for%20similar%20goods.%3Cp%3EScott%20Olson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETJX's%20CEO%20says%20the%20off-price%20retailer%20isn't%20immune%20to%20tariffs%2C%20but%20it%20does%20have%20strategies%20to%20help.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20credited%20the%20company's%20planning%20and%20allocation%20teams%20for%20getting%20the%20right%20goods%20to%20shoppers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20he%20sees%20other%20retailers%20raising%20prices%20gradually%2C%20rather%20than%20all%20at%20once%2C%20when%20tariffs%20hit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETJX%20continues%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftjx-ceo-tariffs-creating-textbook-buying-opportunity-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20the%20big%20winners%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20trade%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20parent%20company%20of%20off-price%20retail%20chains%20like%20T.J.%20Maxx%2C%20Marshalls%2C%20Home%20Goods%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsierra-trading-post-store-fast-growing-brand-tjx-companies-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESierra%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20while%20the%20company%20isn't%20immune%20to%20the%20impact%20of%20this%20year's%20tariffs%2C%20it%20does%20have%20several%20strategies%20that%20have%20helped%20soften%20the%20blow%20and%20keep%20sales%20and%20profits%20strong.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETJX%20beat%20expectations%20for%20the%20second%20quarter%20with%204%25%20comparable%20sales%20growth%20and%20a%20pretax%20profit%20margin%20of%2011.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20one%20of%20those%20funky%20situations%20where%20we%20don't%20top-down%20dictate%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20CEO%20Ernie%20Herrman%20in%20the%20company's%20quarterly%20earnings%20call%20on%20Wednesday.%20He%20said%20the%20company%20relies%20on%20beating%20other%20retailers'%20%26quot%3Bout-the-door%20pricing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-are-tariffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESince%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20effectively%20taxes%20on%20foreign%20goods%20imported%20into%20a%20country%2C%20and%20TJX%20mostly%20buys%20its%20merchandise%20from%20brands%20that%20have%20already%20paid%20those%20fees%2C%20the%20company%20has%20little%20influence%20over%20how%20the%20additional%20cost%20is%20handled.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerrman%20said%20the%20company%20directly%20imports%20a%20small%20share%20%E2%80%94%20about%2010%25%20%E2%80%94%20of%20what%20it%20sells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETJX's%20focus%20on%20competitors'%20pricing%20gives%20Herrman%20unique%20insight%20into%20how%20tariffs%20are%20rolling%20out%20through%20the%20consumer%20economy.%20Retailers%20like%20Walmart%2C%20Home%20Depot%2C%20and%20Macy's%20have%20said%20they'll%20have%20to%20raise%20prices%20on%20certain%20items%20due%20to%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20some%20retailers%20don't%20seem%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bmoving%20the%20price%20directly%20with%20the%20first%20landing%20of%20the%20tariff%26quot%3B%20but%20rather%20doing%20so%20%26quot%3Bin%20steps.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20you're%20going%20to%20see%20a%20more%20of%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20gradual%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-raising-prices-increases-trump-tariffs-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eincrease%20in%20pricing%20as%20the%20tariffs%20come%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20want%20to%2C%20I%20think%2C%20turn%20off%20customers%20immediately%20by%20seeing%20a%20dramatic%20price%20shift.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20TJX%20does%20differently%2C%20Herrman%20said%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Baggressively%26quot%3B%20compare%20prices%20and%20promotions%20with%20other%20retailers%20for%20every%20item%20it%20sells%2C%20and%20then%20negotiate%20a%20price%20it%20is%20willing%20to%20pay%20based%20on%20what%20a%20shopper%20would%20spend%20elsewhere%20for%20similar%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20absolutely%20a%20deal-by-deal%2C%20SKU-by-SKU%2C%20brand-by-brand%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Herrman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20navigating%20in%20the%20tariff%20environment%20by%20just%20staying%20simple%20and%20pure%20to%20that%20model%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20TJX%20won't%20ever%20raise%20prices%2C%20but%20this%20approach%20aims%20to%20keep%20TJX%20prices%20comfortably%20below%20what%20other%20retailers%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20tariffs%20prevent%20TJX%20buyers%20from%20negotiating%20a%20favorable%20deal%20on%20a%20particular%20product%2C%20Herrman%20said%20the%20company%20simply%20won't%20carry%20as%20much%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20gives%20TJX's%20merchandising%20and%20buying%20teams%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20credit%2C%20Herrman%20said%20the%20unsung%20heroes%20in%20the%20TJX%20family%20are%20the%20brands'%20planning%20and%20allocation%20teams%2C%20who%20determine%20what%20goods%20to%20put%20in%20which%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20planning%20and%20allocation%20division%20is%20so%20good%20at%20balancing%20our%20mixes%20by%20category%2C%20family%20of%20business%20%E2%80%94%20literally%20by%20district%2C%20by%20store%2C%26quot%3B%20Herrman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20buyers%20find%20the%20good%20deals%20from%20suppliers%2C%20but%20it's%20allocators%20who%20get%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A